FEJIX STYLE RULES:
PREFIX_PascalCase -- Normal style
PREFIX_SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE -- Macros, constants
snake_case -- local variables, struct members
_snake_case -- private struct members

########################################

PREFIXES:

FJ -- Normal Fejix declaration

Example:
-------------------------------
FJ_Init
FJ_NewWidget
FJ_SomeThingElse
-------------------------------

FJF -- Fejix flag

Example:
-------------------------------
#ifdef FJF_BACKEND_SDL
    // Do SDL-specific stuff
#else
    // Do something else
#endif
-------------------------------


FJI -- Implementation-specific but not backend-specific
Used only within Fejix files

Example:
-------------------------------
typedef struct FJI_Widget
{
    //...
    struct FJI_Widget *some_ptr;
    //...
} FJ_Widget;
-------------------------------


FJH -- Header guard prefix

Example:
-------------------------------
#ifndef FJH_WIDGET
#define FJH_WIDGET
//...
#endif
-------------------------------


FJK -- Backend-specific
Discouraged to use unless you guard it with #ifdef FJF_BACKEND_...
